in einer kritischen Edition vorgelegt, darunter drei Briefe des Patriarchen Germanos I. aus den Anfängen des Bilderstreits.  aThe second volume of the three-volume edition (the first volume was published in 2008) continues the edition of the proceedings of the Seventh Ecumenical Council of 787 (Nicaenum II) which dealt with the controversy surrounding the veneration of images (Iconoclastic Controversy). In addition to an introduction which describes the transmission of the proceedings, it contains the Greek text of the 3rd and 4th sessions of the council, confronting these with the Latin translation of Anastasius Bibliothecarius in 873. The detailed critical apparatus also references source texts and parallel texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600vEarly works to 1800. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600vSources. 0aCouncils and synods, EcumenicalvSources. 4a7. ökumenisches Konzil 787. 4aBilderstreit. 4aByzanz. 4aKonzilsakten. 4aNicaenum II. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  a7th Ecumenical Council 787.  aByzantium.  aCouncil Acts.  aIconoclastic Controversy.  aNicaenum II.1 aLamberz, Erich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE,RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2012z9783110288957oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311027274140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027280240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110272802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/